paper_title: Learning nonlinear operators in latent spaces for real-time predictions of complex dynamics in physical systems

claims.claim: For random seed 2, the prediction accuracy of Latent DeepONet, measured in terms of mean squared error (MSE) is 0.000184 / 0.000175 / 0.000163 / 0.000163 for latent dimensions d = 9 / 25 / 49 / 64.
instruction: Create an Anaconda Python 3.8 virtual environment.
Install dependencies in the 'requirements.txt' via pip.

claims.claim: For random seed 12, the prediction accuracy of Latent DeepONet, measured in terms of mean squared error (MSE) is 0.000126 / 0.000143 / 0.000130 / 0.000172 for latent dimensions d = 9 / 25 / 49 / 64.
For random seed 22, the prediction accuracy of Latent DeepONet, measured in terms of mean squared error (MSE) is 0.000125 / 0.000133 / 0.000133 / 0.000137 for latent dimensions d = 9 / 25 / 49 / 64.
For random seed 32, the prediction accuracy of Latent DeepONet, measured in terms of mean squared error (MSE) is 0.000144 / 0.000134 / 0.000140 / 0.000125 for latent dimensions d = 9 / 25 / 49 / 64.
For random seed 42, the prediction accuracy of Latent DeepONet, measured in terms of mean squared error (MSE) is 0.000139 / 0.000145 / 0.000125 / 0.000225 for latent dimensions d = 9 / 25 / 49 / 64.
